The paper discusses the use of crowdsourcing for information extraction tasks, which is a common topic in the fields of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and computational linguistics (cs.CL). The specific tasks mentioned in the paper, such as event detection and relation extraction, are also relevant to the sub-categories of cybernetics (cs.CY) and information retrieval (cs.IR). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of human annotators and the challenges associated with their participation, which is relevant to the sub-category of human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
